Reasoning: The paper discusses an enhanced version of XP methodology for large-scale projects, which falls under the category of software engineering. Therefore, cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the discipline of systems engineering, which could fall under cs.SD (Systems and Control). The use of moderation principles and management principles of reorganizing companies could also relate to cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). Finally, the mention of telecommunication industry and IT technology consultancy firms could relate to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
